VIEW OUR PORTFOLIO OF COMPANIES






 
 
 



 


Rubicon :: Our investment focus



















 
 



our investment focus
Rubicon Partners focuses on situations with transactional or operational complexity; situations which demand a differentiated investor capable of supplementing capital investment with operational and strategic support 






Long-term investors
Average investment hold:> 7 years 

Hands-on experienced approach
Support management with rigorous financial control
Strategy planning and investment for growth 

Manufacturing, distribution and service businesses in industrial end markets 

Acquisition of complex industrial businesses, individual companies and portfolios 

Enterprise value: £15m to £250m 

Succession issues
Carve-outs
Portfolio complexity
Strategic repositioning 





 

 
 



 


Rubicon :: Investment Vehicles



















 
 


our investment vehicles

Over the last 23 years Rubicon Partners has invested approximately £750million. We currently operate through three investment vehicles.


 


VIEW ACQUISITIONS:

RG INDUSTRIES LLP
RPI LLP
TRIO GROUP

  




rubicon grovepoint industries llp
Rubicon Grovepoint Industries LLP (RGI) is an investment partnership with Grovepoint Capital and Investec Acquisition Finance, formed in 2011. RGI’s focus is on acquisitions of individual businesses challenged by complexity in the manufacturing and distribution sectors.




rubicon partners Industries llp
Rubicon Partners Industries LLP (RPI) is an industrial holding company established in 2003 wholly owned by Rubicon Partners. It focuses on add-on acquisitions to existing companies and new investments which do not overlap with other vehicles.




trio group
Trio was established in 2011 as an investment partnership with Vision Capital. The focus is on acquiring portfolios of industrial businesses in the DACH region from industrial groups or private equity.




 

 
 



